<paragraph id="8BB39B5EFFB9FFE2FF2878B046535433" blockId="7.[174,1233,1742,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
Рис. 4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFB9FFE2FF7078B046E355E3" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[246,430,1744,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FF7078B046E355E3" box="[246,430,1744,1766]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Eupyrgota unicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, голотип Ơ: 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FDA878B0457455E3" box="[558,569,1744,1766]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">1</emphasis>
— общий вид, слева; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FC9D78B0440E55E0" box="[795,835,1744,1766]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">2 —</emphasis>
этикетки; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FC3478B0449955E3" box="[946,980,1744,1766]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">3, 4</emphasis>
— голова (
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FBCD78B0431B55E3" box="[1099,1110,1744,1766]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">3</emphasis>
— спереди, 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FF28788A47F45405" box="[174,185,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">4</emphasis>
— слева); 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FEAE788A467E5405" box="[296,307,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">5</emphasis>
— крыло; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FE22788A46E25405" box="[420,431,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">6</emphasis>
— среднеспинка, сверху; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FD3D788A458B5405" box="[699,710,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">7</emphasis>
— переднее бедро; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FC12788A44D25405" box="[916,927,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">8</emphasis>
— среднее бедро; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FBD9788A43275405" box="[1119,1130,1770,1792]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">9</emphasis>
— заднее бедро; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FF7079654640541E" box="[246,269,1797,1819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">10</emphasis>
— брюшко, сверху; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FE65796546B7541E" box="[483,506,1797,1819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">11</emphasis>
— основной членик яйцеклада, сбоку и снизу; 
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB9FFE2FC6A7965434E541E" box="[1004,1027,1797,1819]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">12</emphasis>
— то же, щетинки, увеличено.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB39B5EFFB6FFEDFF5D7ECF44BC524F" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
R e m a r k s. The presence of reduced basal pair of sctl and slender hooks of oviscape support its placement to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFB6FFEDFE5F7EB0453553EC" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1942" box="[473,632,208,233]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Taeniomastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB6FFEDFE5F7EB0453553EC" box="[473,632,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Taeniomastix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only 
<typeStatus id="54B725FCFFB6FFEDFD7B7EAF441553EF" box="[765,856,207,234]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFB6FFEDFC027EB044B753EC" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1934" box="[900,1018,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB6FFEDFC027EB044B753EC" box="[900,1018,207,234]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">A. facialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hendel has not indicated the number of type specimens) is a teneral specimen with collapsed head and brown abdominal and thoracal pattern, but otherwise shows no differences from types of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFB6FFEDFF207F50465F524C" authorityName="Kim, Han" authorityYear="2000" box="[166,274,304,329]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB6FFEDFF207F50465F524C" box="[166,274,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">E. tigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and I consider then conspecific and synonymize these names.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB39B5EFFB6FFEDFF207F304505526F" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,362]" box="[166,584,335,362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicName id="4C0CE0DDFFB6FFEDFF207F304505526F" authority="(Vanschuytbroeck, 1963)" baseAuthorityName="Vanschuytbroeck" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[166,584,335,362]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saegeri">
<emphasis id="B978474CFFB6FFEDFF207F304655526C" bold="true" box="[166,280,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">E. saegeri</emphasis>
(Vanschuytbroeck, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
